# API Keys Registry — <PROJECT-ID>

All keys follow the convention: `CRISPAI-<VENDOR>-<PROJECT-ID>`

## Keys Required for This Project

Add these to `~/.claude/settings.json` under the `env` block before starting work.

```json
{
  "env": {
    "CRISPAI-GEMINI-<PROJECT-ID>":    "<provision at aistudio.google.com>",
    "CRISPAI-NEBIUS-<PROJECT-ID>":    "<provision at studio.nebius.com>",
    "CRISPAI-OPENAI-<PROJECT-ID>":    "<provision at platform.openai.com>",
    "CRISPAI-ANTHROPIC-<PROJECT-ID>": "<provision at console.anthropic.com>",
    "CRISPAI-GITHUB-<PROJECT-ID>":    "<provision at github.com/settings/tokens>"
  }
}
```

## Key Status

| Key | Status | Used For |
|-----|--------|----------|
| `CRISPAI-GEMINI-<PROJECT-ID>` | [ ] provisioned | Web search, light research (flash-lite) |
| `CRISPAI-NEBIUS-<PROJECT-ID>` | [ ] provisioned | Embeddings overflow, batch writing, fast structured output |
| `CRISPAI-OPENAI-<PROJECT-ID>` | [ ] provisioned | GPT-4o fallback, embeddings fallback |
| `CRISPAI-ANTHROPIC-<PROJECT-ID>` | [ ] provisioned | Final QA, tool use, assembly (claude-sonnet-4-6) |
| `CRISPAI-GITHUB-<PROJECT-ID>` | [ ] provisioned | GitHub API, repo automation |

## Nebius Endpoint
```
Base URL: https://api.studio.nebius.com/v1/
Auth:     Bearer $CRISPAI-NEBIUS-<PROJECT-ID>
Protocol: OpenAI-compatible
```

## Verify All Keys
```bash
for key in \
  CRISPAI-GEMINI-<PROJECT-ID> \
  CRISPAI-NEBIUS-<PROJECT-ID> \
  CRISPAI-OPENAI-<PROJECT-ID> \
  CRISPAI-ANTHROPIC-<PROJECT-ID> \
  CRISPAI-GITHUB-<PROJECT-ID>; do
  val=$(printenv "$key")
  echo "$key: ${val:+SET}${val:-MISSING}"
done
```
